( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 32=

3
00:01:38,066 --> 00:01:39,460
I'll send you a WeChat contact.

4
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,377
Zhao Lanxin from Colorful Culture Media.

5
00:01:42,511 --> 00:01:44,200
She likes Order of the Mountain Ghost,

6
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:45,740
and she reached out to me.

7
00:01:47,555 --> 00:01:48,500
You said it yourself.

8
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:49,700
She's my rival.

9
00:01:50,660 --> 00:01:53,100
So there's no way
she's taking over this novel to help me.

10
00:01:54,822 --> 00:01:56,222
Throwing in the towel?

11
00:01:57,300 --> 00:01:57,820
Yeah.

12
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:00,380
I didn't expect you to concede so fast.

13
00:02:01,022 --> 00:02:02,800
You care about winning and losing.

14
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:03,580
I don't.

15
00:02:04,311 --> 00:02:05,466
What do you care about then?

16
00:02:06,260 --> 00:02:08,300
I don't want to live with regrets

17
00:02:08,888 --> 00:02:10,288
or a guilty conscience.

18
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:13,820
You need to win first
before anything else matters.

19
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,920
I care about
my relationships with people.

20
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:17,780
I care about how others feel.

21
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:19,340
But you don't.

22
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,660
If nobody cared about how I felt,

23
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:23,580
why should I care about theirs?

24
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:25,460
No.

25
00:02:26,660 --> 00:02:28,980
I care about people
who envy or are jealous of me.

26
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,300
Or maybe you do care,

27
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:37,860
but you pretend not to.

28
00:02:39,488 --> 00:02:41,177
Don't need to worry about me.

29
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:42,740
I'm the winner here.

30
00:02:43,355 --> 00:02:44,711
What are you going to do?

31
00:02:44,822 --> 00:02:46,340
Drive ride-hailing cars with He Han?

32
00:02:46,644 --> 00:02:48,155
I haven't figured it out yet.

33
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:50,420
There's a lot left to wrap up

34
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,180
at the company.

35
00:02:52,688 --> 00:02:54,111
Why did you come to me?

36
00:02:57,377 --> 00:02:58,740
I want to ask you for a favor.

37
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:01,377
How do you know I would help you?

38
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,420
You would enjoy helping me.

39
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,180
It makes you feel

40
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:06,900
you're above me.

41
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,260
What is it?

42
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:17,111
I want to hand Order
of the Mountain Ghost over to you.

43
00:03:18,088 --> 00:03:19,133
I'm not interested.

44
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:20,940
That's why I'm asking for help.

45
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:25,540
After the novel is finished,

46
00:03:25,660 --> 00:03:27,222
whether you renew his contract or not,

47
00:03:27,244 --> 00:03:27,977
I won't interfere.

48
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:29,500
That's between you and him.

49
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:31,060
But right now,

50
00:03:31,620 --> 00:03:32,700
I hope you can assign him

51
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:33,660
a good editor

52
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:35,533
and help him finish the novel properly.

53
00:03:35,555 --> 00:03:36,911
I can't guarantee rankings.

54
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,533
Top ten shouldn't be a problem,

55
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:39,820
to be fair.

56
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,340
That means you owe me one.

57
00:03:45,740 --> 00:03:47,140
I don't want him to know

58
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:49,540
you took on the novel as a favor.

59
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:53,740
An author's pride matters a lot.

60
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:54,780
Understood.

61
00:03:55,022 --> 00:03:56,460
I'll say I took an interest in it.

62
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:58,300
Thank you.

63
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:03,300
Lin Zhanqiao,

64
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:04,980
you're a good person.

65
00:04:05,888 --> 00:04:07,500
I'm genuinely envious of you for that.

66
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:09,180
It's not flattery.

67
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,060
It just means
you've been treated kindly.

68
00:04:33,155 --> 00:04:34,066
Where's Dad?

69
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:36,500
I kicked him out.

70
00:04:37,911 --> 00:04:39,177
He has nowhere to go.

71
00:04:42,020 --> 00:04:43,060
That's exactly why

72
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,260
I kicked him out.

73
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:47,220
When he has nowhere left to go,

74
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:49,380
he'll regret

75
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:51,180
abandoning you and me

76
00:04:52,180 --> 00:04:53,780
to fool around with those women outside.

77
00:04:55,940 --> 00:04:57,060
Once he has nowhere to live,

78
00:04:57,488 --> 00:04:59,555
he'll start coveting the apartment
you live in now.

79
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,740
This apartment's partly
under his name too.

80
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:05,140
The nerve of him
to ask me for that apartment.

81
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:06,800
Where's he going to stay then?

82
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:07,180
He...

83
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,180
He can come beg for

84
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:11,460
our forgiveness.

85
00:05:15,222 --> 00:05:16,220
What do you mean?

86
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:17,900
Haven't we been waiting

87
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:21,260
for an apology and repentance from him

88
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:22,740
all these years?

89
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:26,260
Now he's old

90
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,340
and broke.

91
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:30,060
He should beg us.

92
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:36,460
That's what you want.

93
00:05:37,444 --> 00:05:39,020
I stopped thinking that way long ago.

94
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:40,540
I didn't know

95
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:41,980
you still thought like that.

96
00:05:42,355 --> 00:05:43,980
What have you been doing
all these years?

97
00:05:44,288 --> 00:05:45,660
Waiting for him to come back?

98
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:47,220
I knew

99
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:49,460
this day would come eventually.

100
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,060
And then what?

101
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:53,740
You would forgive him

102
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,500
and live with him again?

103
00:05:56,620 --> 00:05:57,620
That depends on

104
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,860
how sincere his apology
and repentance are.

105
00:06:04,888 --> 00:06:06,600
He treated you badly for so many years,

106
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,860
and one moment of repentance

107
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:10,940
can wipe everything clean?

108
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:16,020
Other than us,

109
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:19,620
no one else is going
to take care of him.

110
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,900
In the end,

111
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:25,540
he'll only

112
00:06:26,780 --> 00:06:27,860
grow old alone.

113
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:30,780
That's his own choice.

114
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,540
I don't need his apology or repentance.

115
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:38,140
And I'll never forgive him.

116
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:40,340
So when you say these things,

117
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:41,460
don't involve me.

118
00:06:41,688 --> 00:06:44,044
Whether he comes back or not
has nothing to do with me.

119
00:06:44,844 --> 00:06:46,020
Giving him a place to stay

120
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:47,550
doesn't mean I'll live with him again.

121
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:49,511
I'm not going to eat with him
or talk to him either.

122
00:06:50,420 --> 00:06:52,180
I'll only support him in his old age

123
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:53,844
based on the standard of a nursing home.

124
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,780
After all, legally, I'm his daughter.

125
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:59,020
But I won't cry for him.

126
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:10,580
Do you have to oppose

127
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:12,700
everything I say on purpose?

128
00:07:13,620 --> 00:07:15,540
Are you trying to rebel against me?

129
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:17,740
I'm not.

130
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:23,020
It's just that
we have different opinions

131
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,260
about Lawyer Bei and my dad.

132
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:28,380
You still have the nerve
to bring him up?

133
00:07:35,020 --> 00:07:36,340
Is this dress

134
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:37,860
from him?

135
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:40,460
You planned to wear it

136
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:42,180
to Bali

137
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,100
and announce

138
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:47,140
your relationship, right?

139
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,860
I won't allow it.

140
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:17,460
Is this all you can do?

141
00:08:24,466 --> 00:08:26,230
There are plenty of nice dresses
out there.

142
00:08:26,711 --> 00:08:28,422
You can't tear them all apart.

143
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:31,980
Where are you going?

144
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:33,220
To buy a dress.

145
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:52,820
Did your mom leave?

146
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:55,020
I'll get you a hotel.

147
00:08:55,177 --> 00:08:56,044
I'll pay for it.

148
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:56,900
What hotel?

149
00:08:58,820 --> 00:08:59,900
Look at you now.

150
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:02,230
You can only stay somewhere
for around 200 yuan a night.

151
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:05,020
Then I'm not going.

152
00:09:09,180 --> 00:09:09,900
Fine, stay here.

153
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:28,820
Zhou Mei!

154
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:30,340
Zhou Mei!

155
00:09:31,866 --> 00:09:32,820
Changed your mind?

156
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:34,420
Your mom called.

157
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,700
She said you wouldn't answer her calls.

158
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,060
And if you go to Bali,
she'll jump off the building.

159
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,980
Where are you, Zhanqiao?

160
00:10:18,460 --> 00:10:19,180
Can you come over?

161
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,955
My mom's threatening to jump.

162
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:21,940
At my place.

163
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:22,940
Okay.

164
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:35,220
Taxi!

165
00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:37,420
Sorry, can I take this cab?

166
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:38,577
I need to save someone.

167
00:10:55,444 --> 00:10:56,355
She's not here.

168
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,260
Hello, police officer?

169
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,666
I want to report an emergency.

170
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:20,420
Mom!

171
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:22,260
Mom!

172
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:24,100
Mom.

173
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:31,300
I've written my will.

174
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:34,140
When the time comes, everyone will know

175
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,940
I was driven to death

176
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:39,980
by my own daughter.

177
00:11:40,580 --> 00:11:40,980
Mom,

178
00:11:41,860 --> 00:11:42,580
come down.

179
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:44,260
I told you before.

180
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:48,500
If you stayed with Lawyer Bei,

181
00:11:50,060 --> 00:11:51,420
I would die right in front of you.

182
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:57,044
She's trying to take her own life.

183
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:58,340
Give in to her now.

184
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:05,300
Is that man

185
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:08,540
more important

186
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:10,540
than my life?

187
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,940
(Emergency)

188
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:19,380
(Rescue Operation)

189
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:20,780
Don't crowd around!

190
00:12:20,822 --> 00:12:21,500
Watch your step.

191
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,911
- What's going on?
- Alright. Stop looking.

192
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,140
Back up.

193
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:26,860
Back up.

194
00:12:26,860 --> 00:12:28,180
This looks dangerous.

195
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,300
Excuse me. Make way.

196
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:30,500
Excuse me, can I get through?

197
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,410
You can't go in.

198
00:12:31,410 --> 00:12:32,222
It's dangerous.

199
00:12:35,222 --> 00:12:36,660
What's there to be so upset about?

200
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:39,780
I won't be with him anymore.

201
00:12:40,380 --> 00:12:41,300
You're lying to me!

202
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:42,780
I'm not lying!

203
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:45,460
I don't believe
anything you say anymore!

204
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,260
Only if I die in front of you

205
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:50,180
will you stop seeing him.

206
00:12:50,577 --> 00:12:52,180
Because every time you're with him,

207
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:54,860
you'll think about me jumping today!

208
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:58,700
You forced me into this.

209
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:00,820
And you too, Zhou.

210
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,580
This is all

211
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:05,100
because of you.

212
00:13:05,533 --> 00:13:07,020
You won't get to live in peace either.

213
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:08,700
Mom, I won't see him again!

214
00:13:09,660 --> 00:13:10,940
You won't?

215
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,740
How are you going to prove it?

216
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:16,220
I'll prove it to you.

217
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:17,777
Come down first.

218
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:18,620
Come down.

219
00:13:18,620 --> 00:13:20,180
This will never happen again!

220
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:23,220
You'll never have to worry
about this again.

221
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:26,060
If I come down,

222
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:29,100
and you break your promise,

223
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:31,780
I'll jump again.

224
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:33,420
I know.

225
00:13:36,180 --> 00:13:37,460
That's why I'll prove it to you.

226
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:40,340
Come down first.

227
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:43,820
You're my mom.

228
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:45,900
And he's my dad.

229
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:51,222
I can't let you kill yourself

230
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:55,460
in front of him because of me.

231
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:03,060
You...

232
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:04,340
You...

233
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:08,140
You finally understand now.

234
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:13,100
Mom.

235
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:17,260
Mom.

236
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:22,180
Come.

237
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:26,955
Come here.

238
00:14:39,444 --> 00:14:40,300
It's too dangerous.

239
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:44,140
You really understand now?

240
00:14:46,340 --> 00:14:47,140
I do.

241
00:14:55,444 --> 00:14:55,940
Come down.

242
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:56,580
Slowly.

243
00:15:05,244 --> 00:15:06,060
You come down, too.

244
00:15:08,780 --> 00:15:09,460
Hurry.

245
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:11,820
Mom.

246
00:15:16,860 --> 00:15:18,620
You said that ever since
you married my dad,

247
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:23,340
you've never been happy.

248
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:28,620
But ever since I was born,

249
00:15:31,460 --> 00:15:32,940
I've never been happy, either.

250
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:12,300
Zhou Mei!

251
00:17:03,140 --> 00:17:07,940
(Emergency, Ambulance)

252
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:14,140
(Emergency Rescue Room)

253
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:15,580
She's your daughter!

254
00:17:15,644 --> 00:17:17,380
What did you say to her? What did you do

255
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:18,580
to make her jump?

256
00:17:19,780 --> 00:17:21,460
I've never seen parents like you before!

257
00:17:21,580 --> 00:17:23,140
You don't deserve to be her parents!

258
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:24,700
Is she going to be okay?

259
00:17:25,820 --> 00:17:26,380
Doctor.

260
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:28,100
The patient is awake.

261
00:17:28,980 --> 00:17:29,900
How is she?

262
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:31,333
She sprained her ankle

263
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,450
and has a mild concussion.

264
00:17:32,460 --> 00:17:33,333
Nothing serious.

265
00:17:34,740 --> 00:17:35,260
Thank you.

266
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:38,020
Thank you so much.

267
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:43,660
I believe you now.

268
00:17:45,380 --> 00:17:46,180
Let's just pretend

269
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:48,980
none of this ever happened,

270
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:50,540
okay?

271
00:17:56,740 --> 00:17:57,180
Zhou Mei,

272
00:17:58,580 --> 00:17:59,580
say something.

273
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,060
Zhou Mei,

274
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:18,660
I spent my whole life

275
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:20,266
not understanding what family meant.

276
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:21,940
But...

277
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:25,220
when you jumped today,

278
00:18:25,820 --> 00:18:27,180
I finally understood.

279
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:30,700
Maybe I realized it too late.

280
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:33,140
Talking to you about family now

281
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:35,900
would only burden you.

282
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:43,580
But I hope you'll live well from now on.

283
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:46,060
You're still young.

284
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,060
When you jumped just now,

285
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:51,777
if there hadn't been
an air cushion below,

286
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:53,620
I would've jumped

287
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:55,020
with you.

288
00:18:57,060 --> 00:18:58,180
We've been through

289
00:18:58,940 --> 00:19:01,500
everything together all these years.

290
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,380
Your daughter Zhou Mei
has already died.

291
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:10,955
I don't want to talk to
either of you anymore.

292
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:14,500
I want to see Lin Zhanqiao.

293
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:32,540
You really scared me, you know?

294
00:19:33,220 --> 00:19:34,380
Even if they're your parents,

295
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:35,700
they're not worth this.

296
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:36,860
No one is.

297
00:19:37,044 --> 00:19:38,260
You're absolutely not allowed

298
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,288
to think about doing something
like this again. Okay?

299
00:19:42,860 --> 00:19:43,660
I won't anymore.

300
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,180
I've given

301
00:19:49,340 --> 00:19:50,540
the old Zhou Mei back to them.

302
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:53,380
From now on,

303
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:55,140
I belong to myself.

304
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:06,820
You can't fight them

305
00:20:06,820 --> 00:20:07,820
this way.

306
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:11,500
If anything happens,
you can come to me.

307
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:13,500
We'll figure it out together.

308
00:20:14,888 --> 00:20:17,066
The last thirty years
may not have been good,

309
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:19,780
but we still have many more years
ahead of us.

310
00:20:21,820 --> 00:20:23,220
We can live well together.

311
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:49,220
So now,

312
00:20:50,780 --> 00:20:52,140
do you regret

313
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:55,180
what you did back then?

314
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:00,620
If you had another chance,

315
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:03,220
would you

316
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:06,020
still leave our daughter and me?

317
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:07,700
Yes.

318
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,060
Our marriage was a mistake.

319
00:21:16,260 --> 00:21:16,940
So leaving us

320
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:20,140
for those women who deceived you

321
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:21,660
was the right choice?

322
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:29,100
Maybe that was a mistake, too.

323
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:32,540
Now you're broken and alone.

324
00:21:33,555 --> 00:21:35,155
Where are you going to find a woman

325
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:36,900
who's willing to take you in?

326
00:22:36,180 --> 00:22:37,460
How's Mei, Ms. Lin?

327
00:22:39,088 --> 00:22:40,340
She has a mild concussion.

328
00:22:40,777 --> 00:22:43,044
She should be fine
after resting for a few days.

329
00:22:44,620 --> 00:22:45,260
Why did she...

330
00:22:47,220 --> 00:22:49,140
She was trying to pull her mom back,

331
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:51,820
and then accidentally slipped.

332
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:54,340
That was terrifying.

333
00:22:54,488 --> 00:22:56,890
Good thing you called
the fire department ahead of time

334
00:22:56,890 --> 00:22:58,266
and got everything prepared.

335
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:03,940
Why have you been leaving early
these days?

336
00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:05,333
What have you been up to?

337
00:23:06,540 --> 00:23:07,220
I...

338
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:10,060
I've been out writing novels.

339
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:12,100
Writing novels?

340
00:23:17,780 --> 00:23:18,980
Back when

341
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:21,500
I still had work at the company,

342
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:23,700
I was worried you'd think I wasn't

343
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:24,820
taking my job seriously

344
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:25,940
if I told you.

345
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:28,380
But now the company

346
00:23:28,822 --> 00:23:30,200
is about to shut down,

347
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:31,420
so I figured

348
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:33,060
I should tell you.

349
00:23:34,244 --> 00:23:36,400
You want to become a web novelist?

350
00:23:40,577 --> 00:23:42,020
You've seen so many web novelists

351
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:44,100
rise and fall over the years.

352
00:23:45,140 --> 00:23:45,900
And you know

353
00:23:46,260 --> 00:23:47,420
most of them

354
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,900
just fade into obscurity in the end.

355
00:23:50,140 --> 00:23:51,380
Why do you still want to do it?

356
00:24:02,060 --> 00:24:02,500
Because

357
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:05,580
if I can write

358
00:24:05,580 --> 00:24:07,180
really good stories one day,

359
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:09,500
maybe

360
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:12,700
Mr. He Han

361
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:14,140
will value me more.

362
00:24:16,133 --> 00:24:17,733
Doesn't he already value you?

363
00:24:21,340 --> 00:24:22,100
I...

364
00:24:23,620 --> 00:24:26,020
I don't want to just be his fan.

365
00:24:37,620 --> 00:24:38,820
I hope

366
00:24:38,820 --> 00:24:40,755
one day I can stand on equal footing
with him.

367
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:47,980
Once the company shuts down,

368
00:24:48,511 --> 00:24:50,140
I probably shouldn't stay here anymore.

369
00:24:51,180 --> 00:24:52,380
This is your house.

370
00:24:53,140 --> 00:24:53,660
Don't.

371
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:54,900
You can stay here.

372
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:55,940
I'll rent it to you.

373
00:24:55,940 --> 00:24:56,810
I'll move out instead.

374
00:24:56,820 --> 00:24:58,900
Who moves out of their own house?

375
00:25:00,180 --> 00:25:01,180
Ask your dad

376
00:25:01,180 --> 00:25:02,980
to help me find another good place.

377
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:04,420
Alright.

378
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:05,300
One bedroom?

379
00:25:06,180 --> 00:25:06,620
Two.

380
00:25:07,020 --> 00:25:08,660
I should leave a room for Zhou Mei.

381
00:25:10,060 --> 00:25:12,380
I really envy Mei for having
a best friend like you.

382
00:25:12,940 --> 00:25:14,820
She would envy you
for having a good father.

383
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,420
Are you okay?

384
00:25:57,220 --> 00:25:58,260
Why didn't you tell me

385
00:25:58,260 --> 00:25:59,888
something this serious had happened?

386
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:01,460
It's fine now.

387
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:12,100
You said it was an accident.

388
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:15,180
From what I heard, it wasn't.

389
00:26:15,180 --> 00:26:16,020
It was an accident.

390
00:26:17,688 --> 00:26:19,177
I was just lucky to survive.

391
00:26:31,666 --> 00:26:32,555
By the way...

392
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:35,620
you should take this back.

393
00:26:44,755 --> 00:26:46,200
You can't go to Bali with me

394
00:26:46,540 --> 00:26:48,180
in your condition.

395
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:51,260
Keep the dress.

396
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:53,220
You can wear it after your foot heals.

397
00:26:54,688 --> 00:26:56,177
I don't want to wear it anymore.

398
00:26:58,260 --> 00:26:59,180
Why not?

399
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:04,620
We...

400
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:10,333
Whatever there was between us before,

401
00:27:10,540 --> 00:27:12,155
I don't want it to continue anymore.

402
00:27:15,860 --> 00:27:16,420
But...

403
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:17,940
But things

404
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,860
between us
are finally getting better.

405
00:27:23,940 --> 00:27:24,620
Why...

406
00:27:25,460 --> 00:27:26,900
Why would you give up now?

407
00:27:32,644 --> 00:27:34,222
Before, I could never have had it.

408
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:36,066
So I always wanted it.

409
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:40,460
Family, parents, and love.

410
00:27:41,533 --> 00:27:44,088
I always felt like everyone else
had a better life than I did.

411
00:27:44,780 --> 00:27:45,900
I envied everyone.

412
00:27:48,222 --> 00:27:50,700
My mom used to say my happiness
had been stolen by others.

413
00:27:53,977 --> 00:27:55,888
So I became jealous of
everyone else, too.

414
00:27:57,620 --> 00:27:59,420
And now, I've finally
won love for myself.

415
00:28:02,300 --> 00:28:02,820
I know

416
00:28:05,180 --> 00:28:05,980
that if I wanted it,

417
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:08,420
you could give me a family.

418
00:28:11,380 --> 00:28:12,540
We could even have children.

419
00:28:15,180 --> 00:28:15,700
Exactly.

420
00:28:18,020 --> 00:28:19,100
Isn't that a good thing?

421
00:28:24,888 --> 00:28:26,844
But I don't feel anything anymore.

422
00:28:30,540 --> 00:28:31,660
What do you mean?

423
00:28:36,420 --> 00:28:37,900
I've finally waited for this day.

424
00:28:41,377 --> 00:28:42,622
You're telling me now

425
00:28:43,311 --> 00:28:45,577
that everything I ever wanted
can finally be mine.

426
00:28:47,420 --> 00:28:48,660
But I don't feel anything.

427
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:51,900
Or maybe

428
00:28:53,911 --> 00:28:55,466
this is all the feeling there is.

429
00:28:57,620 --> 00:28:58,060
So...

430
00:29:00,340 --> 00:29:01,340
let's end this.

431
00:29:04,660 --> 00:29:05,740
I want to be alone.

432
00:29:15,220 --> 00:29:17,140
This must just be temporary.

433
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:20,100
Too much has happened recently.

434
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:23,620
You just need some time to yourself.

435
00:29:24,533 --> 00:29:25,800
Once you're feeling better,

436
00:29:25,933 --> 00:29:27,266
I'll come see you again.

437
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:12,500
Please lift your shirt a little.

438
00:30:32,740 --> 00:30:34,300
(Early intrauterine pregnancy, twins)

439
00:30:36,580 --> 00:30:37,940
What does "twins" mean?

440
00:30:38,288 --> 00:30:39,555
It means twins. Literally.

441
00:30:44,700 --> 00:30:46,140
We never said we wanted children.

442
00:30:47,540 --> 00:30:49,100
Weren't you taking birth control pills?

443
00:30:49,100 --> 00:30:51,090
How did you get pregnant
if you were taking them?

444
00:30:51,100 --> 00:30:52,200
And twins on top of that?

445
00:30:52,860 --> 00:30:53,900
Then take it as a surprise.

446
00:30:56,844 --> 00:30:59,088
You never took birth control at all,
did you?

447
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:00,740
You call this a surprise?

448
00:31:02,300 --> 00:31:02,980
This is a shock.

449
00:31:02,980 --> 00:31:04,377
This is deception, you know that?

450
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:06,860
Your grandma is really happy.

451
00:31:07,088 --> 00:31:09,370
She said she always hoped
she'd get to see your children someday.

452
00:31:09,380 --> 00:31:10,300
I'm not ready for this!

453
00:31:10,300 --> 00:31:12,200
And you never gave me the chance
to get ready!

454
00:31:15,540 --> 00:31:16,620
Why don't you want children?

455
00:31:16,940 --> 00:31:17,860
I can have children.

456
00:31:18,644 --> 00:31:21,288
But this is something we're supposed
to face together in the future.

457
00:31:21,340 --> 00:31:22,380
Did you discuss it with me?

458
00:31:23,260 --> 00:31:23,900
Listen.

459
00:31:26,180 --> 00:31:28,220
We can only have children
if I agree to it.

460
00:31:32,580 --> 00:31:33,620
If you don't agree,

461
00:31:33,888 --> 00:31:35,580
I'll go upstairs right now
and tell the doctor

462
00:31:35,580 --> 00:31:36,644
we're not keeping them.

463
00:31:52,940 --> 00:31:53,420
Zhao Lanxin.

464
00:31:56,780 --> 00:31:57,860
I really hate you.

465
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:22,500
According to the contract,

466
00:32:22,577 --> 00:32:24,466
we have two months left on the lease.

467
00:32:24,740 --> 00:32:26,980
If a new tenant moves in
during that time,

468
00:32:27,580 --> 00:32:29,100
our rent can be refunded.

469
00:32:29,580 --> 00:32:30,420
If not,

470
00:32:31,060 --> 00:32:32,700
we'll have to cover it ourselves.

471
00:32:36,777 --> 00:32:39,180
Once you've sorted out the contracts,
give them to Zhangzhu.

472
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:41,340
I already gave them to her.

473
00:32:47,911 --> 00:32:49,088
How are you holding up?

474
00:32:50,540 --> 00:32:51,940
Feeling a little down?

475
00:32:54,133 --> 00:32:55,700
You finally got the property management

476
00:32:55,700 --> 00:32:57,100
to approve you for a parking spot,

477
00:32:57,155 --> 00:32:58,733
and now the company's shutting down.

478
00:33:00,420 --> 00:33:02,260
Parking spots are more in demand
than offices.

479
00:33:02,260 --> 00:33:04,020
I can easily transfer it anytime.

480
00:33:04,420 --> 00:33:04,900
It's fine.

481
00:33:06,088 --> 00:33:07,600
Have you arranged everything

482
00:33:08,380 --> 00:33:09,220
for what comes after?

483
00:33:11,380 --> 00:33:12,020
More or less.

484
00:33:14,422 --> 00:33:16,660
I transferred Prefrontal Cortex
to Zhao Lanxin's side.

485
00:33:17,340 --> 00:33:19,980
So she'll probably let you take over.

486
00:33:22,420 --> 00:33:23,940
I know after you leave here,

487
00:33:24,340 --> 00:33:25,660
you'll probably join Zhao Lanxin.

488
00:33:27,420 --> 00:33:28,060
Ms. Lin...

489
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:31,100
You were the one who gave

490
00:33:31,822 --> 00:33:33,380
the new author list to her, right?

491
00:33:36,955 --> 00:33:37,980
I'm really sorry about

492
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:39,820
the suspicions I had all along
about Fragile.

493
00:33:41,177 --> 00:33:42,700
It wasn't until the day she resigned

494
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:44,177
that I realized it wasn't her.

495
00:33:44,511 --> 00:33:46,555
Only four people had access
to the new author list.

496
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:48,540
You, her, Zhangzhu,

497
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:50,020
and Naobaijin.

498
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:53,300
But Zhangzhu
didn't know Zhao Lanxin.

499
00:33:54,540 --> 00:33:55,460
Before that,

500
00:33:55,820 --> 00:33:57,020
I even suspected Naobaijin.

501
00:33:57,180 --> 00:33:58,740
I never suspected you at all.

502
00:34:05,620 --> 00:34:06,620
Because at Chenxing,

503
00:34:08,466 --> 00:34:10,044
you were the person I trusted most.

504
00:34:16,180 --> 00:34:17,300
How did you figure it out?

505
00:34:21,733 --> 00:34:23,666
You bought an insurance plan recently.

506
00:34:23,733 --> 00:34:26,088
The salesperson was recommended
by Zhao Lanxin, right?

507
00:34:28,420 --> 00:34:29,820
I happened to see her

508
00:34:30,222 --> 00:34:31,977
when she came to the office
to see you.

509
00:34:32,940 --> 00:34:33,380
Ms. Lin.

510
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:36,020
Ms. Lin.

511
00:34:47,580 --> 00:34:47,980
It's true.

512
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:50,820
I really did want to jump ship

513
00:34:50,820 --> 00:34:52,380
to Zhao Lanxin's side.

514
00:34:53,340 --> 00:34:55,420
I thought Chenxing's core
was its authors.

515
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:57,220
And the core of the authors
was He Han.

516
00:34:57,820 --> 00:34:59,620
I thought you would give up
on Chenxing soon.

517
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:01,020
I'm the boss of Chenxing.

518
00:35:01,580 --> 00:35:02,780
I'm the core.

519
00:35:03,420 --> 00:35:04,540
Even now,

520
00:35:04,540 --> 00:35:06,100
I still don't think of it as giving up.

521
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:08,220
It's only a pause.

522
00:35:10,820 --> 00:35:11,800
And that's also why

523
00:35:13,260 --> 00:35:14,540
I decided not to leave.

524
00:35:17,540 --> 00:35:17,900
Ms. Lin,

525
00:35:18,644 --> 00:35:19,866
I realized that you're

526
00:35:21,020 --> 00:35:21,660
really tough

527
00:35:23,220 --> 00:35:23,820
and resilient.

528
00:35:26,260 --> 00:35:27,140
And also,

529
00:35:31,460 --> 00:35:31,900
I...

530
00:35:32,340 --> 00:35:33,980
I truly didn't expect you

531
00:35:35,460 --> 00:35:36,580
to trust me that much.

532
00:35:46,460 --> 00:35:48,540
Ms. Lin, after you found out it was me,

533
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:50,340
why didn't you expose me?

534
00:35:53,580 --> 00:35:55,300
Because you pulled back in time.

535
00:35:55,777 --> 00:35:58,200
You didn't leak the information
about Prefrontal Cortex

536
00:35:58,460 --> 00:35:59,580
to Zhao Lanxin.

537
00:36:00,822 --> 00:36:02,830
That's why the launch of
Order of the Mountain Ghost

538
00:36:02,844 --> 00:36:03,777
went so smoothly.

539
00:36:04,620 --> 00:36:05,650
If Zhao Lanxin had known,

540
00:36:05,650 --> 00:36:07,600
she definitely would've
interfered somehow.

541
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:10,888
I have enough judgment to see that much.

542
00:36:22,460 --> 00:36:24,380
After leaving here,

543
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:25,740
you've decided

544
00:36:25,740 --> 00:36:27,140
to join Zhao Lanxin's company?

545
00:36:29,820 --> 00:36:30,420
Dingqi?

546
00:36:30,820 --> 00:36:31,260
No.

547
00:36:33,340 --> 00:36:34,620
I'm talking with a new company.

548
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:36,140
You know the boss.

549
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:37,940
Who?

550
00:36:38,420 --> 00:36:38,820
Dai Shan.

551
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:43,300
Didn't she already leave Shanghai?

552
00:36:43,940 --> 00:36:44,740
She's back.

553
00:36:45,100 --> 00:36:46,180
She went overseas before

554
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:48,133
to secure investment funding.

555
00:36:57,666 --> 00:36:58,600
Alright then.

556
00:36:59,740 --> 00:37:00,755
Wish you good luck.

557
00:37:05,220 --> 00:37:05,660
I'm sorry,

558
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:06,460
Ms. Lin.

559
00:37:14,780 --> 00:37:15,180
Ms. Lin,

560
00:37:16,940 --> 00:37:18,660
are you staying in this industry?

561
00:37:20,020 --> 00:37:20,740
Of course.

562
00:37:22,660 --> 00:37:24,180
I like this industry.

563
00:37:25,311 --> 00:37:27,622
There are more people here
who love reading and writing.

564
00:37:28,140 --> 00:37:28,940
And more people

565
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,177
with loyalty and tenderness, too.

566
00:38:06,380 --> 00:38:07,260
(As much as I hate)

567
00:38:08,422 --> 00:38:09,866
(seeing each of them off,)

568
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:12,260
(farewells still come.)

569
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,466
(So we might as well learn
from those free-spirited wanderers)

570
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:17,620
(and part ways cleanly.)

571
00:38:18,980 --> 00:38:20,020
(The feelings will stay)

